description: For sale: $674,900. Experience a home with a space work, play, learning and eating...spread out and  enjoy life at home. Freshly painted trim thorughout the main level family room, front entry & breakfast room. Spectacular updated two-story home in the Tanglewood Neighborhood offers gracious living indoors and out.  Enjoy the sunny perennial gardens and manicured lawn in the front yard and slip away to quiet, shady privacy in the back. Deck overlooks towering red and white pine forest with new stamped concrete patio and firepit area below. Hot tub is tucked among pines with easy access from the laundry room.  This light-filled home offers 4 bedrooms on one level, a spacious updated, spa-like owner's suite with a soaking tub and tree-top views. The recently finished lower level features a walk-out family room with bar and guest bedroom with attached 3/4 bath (heated floor, walk-in shower). The Polaris 500, 2012, 4-Wheeler with plow can stay with the house with a strong offer for plowing the new driveway.

description: For sale: $730,000. Spacious 15.4 ac estate hm nestled among multiple state parks brimming w/wildlife & the peacefulness of the quiet valley.  Lrg windows provide a view of the valley year-around & allow natural light to flood through the openness of the vaulted ceilings to accentuate hickory cabinets & woodwork throughout. In-floor heat keeps your feet warm as much as the 2 fireplaces located up & down. A second laundry rm is paired with non-conforming bedrooms, a lrg bonus rm above the garage & a rm all set up for a beauty shop.  A screened gazebo overlooks a beautiful gurgling pond. New roof, siding & well & septic compliant.  An impressive outbuilding comes w/an office,full man cave, kitchen, a wine making rm w/in-floor heat & 10k# car hoist.  May Township provides for hm businesses . There is plenty of pasture space & flat areas for riding arenas & stalls. For wine drinkers, sommeliers & vintners.   Sellers are not accepting showings at this time.

For sale: $499,000. PLEASE WEAR MASKS AND GLOVES WHILE ON PREMISE---This historic, stately home in Marine on 
St. Croix is now available after nearly 50 years of family ownership. Spacious, light filled rooms lookout onto the sweeping front lawn, private drive and wooded views of the St. Croix River Valley. The entry of this traditional home opens to a formal dining room with period built-in cabinetry, living room with fireplace and freshly refinished floors, and sun room and family room beyond. The second floor hosts all 3 bedrooms, including the master suite. The barn has a workshop, tack-room, stables and loft as well as 3 adjacent garage spaces. Walking distance to the Marine General Store, Library, Town Hall and Marina, the property enjoys the proximity of living in town with the quiet and privacy of 8+ acres. This is a perfect opportunity for year-round or seasonal living in this charming village that's just 45 minutes from the Twin Cities.

description:
For sale: $1,200,000. Contact the listing agent, Krista Wolter at 612-247-5106, for additional information and a private showing. The best of old and new can be found here at the historic Asa Parker House in Marine on St. Croix. This home has been completely renovated along with a new addition by Hagstrom Builder and has spared no expense in the remodeling process. Original elements of this home include the front staircase, pocket doors, dormers with arched windows and more. 
Gourmet kitchen has Quartz countertops, high end appliances, center island and walks out to a Bluestone patio for summertime entertaining. Main floor features a bedroom/office, laundry room and 3/4 bath with walk-in shower for main floor living. Dining room and living room with center, two sided fireplace can easily be swapped for personalized living. Lower level has both new space that includes a media/family room and  original area with stone walls for future wine cellar/finished space, plus plenty of room for storage. New 3 car garage. Ready to move in and make this historic property yours to enjoy!

description: For sale: $600,000. This spacious 4200 sq ft Arts & Crafts style home unlike others, is sophisticated in design with exquisite, uncompromising craftsmanship. Recently sold: $1,130,000. The history of this unique property is both interesting and lengthy. For purposes of this narrative and brevity, reference is limited to the original owner.

In 1936 Daniel MacMillan purchased an aging cabin located on the site of the present structure. He and his son Donald spent weekends at the cottage during the summer months where Daniel marveled at the beauty and the quietude of the St. Croix River. It appears little was done to renovate the original cabin. Initially only rugs and good bedding were introduced to the cabin for improved comfort.

After several months of discussions with family members and his son Donald regarding the construction of a more permanent and substantial cottage, Daniel introduced Edwin Lundie to the property to discuss his ideas for building a farmhouse style cottage that would be a "modest little house" but large enough to accommodate family gatherings on weekends.

Lundie was delighted with the spot, remarking that it was ?unconventional and should lend itself to imagination very properly" MacMillan's directive to Lundie "in any event I do not want more than $8,000 $10,000 in this place."

The design Lundie created for the St. Croix River site is a departure from his well-known and recognized designs. The MacMillan's cottage is all stone, quarried on site and assembled with meticulous precision by Irving Peterson. The structure is 77 years old and the stone is tight and solid as the year it was built.

Lundie?s signature design features such a massive fireplace, intricate detail and extensive use of wood paneling and vaulted ceilings are very much in evidence. Very little has been changed and the cottage is intact as originally built with the exception of updated bathrooms and kitchen.  The heating system has been updated and the original cedar shake roof has been replaced with asphalt shingles. 

Contact listing agent for more details...

description: Recently sold: $476,500. This is a beautiful home on Big Marine Lake near Scandia/Marine, MN. There is 100 feet of prime lake shore property and 1 1/2 acres with pond and lots of trees across the road. It is within 15 minutes of either Stillwater/Forest Lake so good for shopping and eating out. Swimming is great with water six feet deep right off the end of the dock and nice sandy area for little ones to swim on shore. Super quiet lake as we are on the bay. Great place to raise a family/ or to bring your grand kids! It is a real clean good small pan fish lake!
